Findings: AP radiograph of the chest was reviewed in comparison to obtained at 02:25 am. The right internal jugular line has been inserted with its tip being at the cavoatrial junction. The NG tube tip passes below the diaphragm terminating in the stomach. The ET tube tip is approximately 6 cm above the carina. Bibasal opacities appear unchanged. Mild pulmonary edema is still present. No pleural effusion or pneumothorax is seen.
